<HEADLINE>
KAOHSIUNG CITY TO BID FOR RIGHT TO ISSUE SPORTS LOTTERY
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kaohsiung,  April 4 (CNA) 04/04/07  19:05:51 (By Lilian Wu)
</P>
<P>
Kaohsiung Mayor Chen Chu said Wednesday that she will convey to
the Executive Yuan the city's hopes of issuing a sports lottery
to help balance the development of southern and northern Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Chen made the remarks during a question-and-answer session at the
Kaohsiung City Council when city councilman Lin Wu-chung of the
ruling Democratic Progressive Party urged the mayor to advocate
for the right to run a sports lottery.
</P>
<P>
Chen promised that the city's Bureau of Finance and Bank of
Kaohsiung will make preparations for such a presentation.
</P>
<P>
She also said that the city government will apply for the right
to run a sports lottery in mid-April, saying that it will help to
promote the 2009 World Games in Kaohsiung and balance regional
development in Taiwan.
</P>
